    "• Establishing an agreement among users where to store sensitive and personal output and recommendations produced by AI-enabled systems [9].",
    "more information, rather than providing a one-off information [54].On the other hand, aligning AI explanations to users' explanations was discouraged in another article [45].",
    "This was because doing so could result in missing opportunities of learning new explanation methods or perspectives from what users already knew.",
    "Instead, this included article suggested to consider other indicators of reliability of explanations, such as alignment with contextual factors in the task domain and leveraging AI-enabled systems to automatically decode relevant information, without relying solely on human input [45].",
